Parliament, Tuesday, 17 September 2019 – President of RSA Cyril Ramaphosa will address a Joint Sitting of both Houses of Parliament - the National Assembly (NA) and the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) on a matter of national importance, violence against women - at 14.00 on Wednesday, 18 September 2019.
	
	The Speaker of the NA, Ms Thandi Modise, and Chairperson of the NCOP, Mr Amos Masondo, will chair and facilitate the special seating called by the President to find a new approach to combatting the high prevalence of violence against women in South Africa.
	
	Section 84 (2) (d) of the Constitution and Rule 7 (1) (b) of the Joint Rules of the National Assembly and National Council of Provinces empower the President to call an extraordinary sitting of the two Houses of Parliament to conduct special business. The President’s address will be followed by a debate of Members of Parliament, as one of the means used by Parliament in executing its mandate of law making, oversight and citizen participation.
	
	DETAILS OF THE JOINT SITTING ARE AS FOLLOWS:
	
	DATE: WEDNESDAY, 18 SEPTEMBER 2019
	TIME: 14:00
	VENUE: NATIONAL ASSEMBLY CHAMBER
	
	Journalists and photographers who do not have Parliamentary media access permits and wish to cover the Joint Sitting should send their details (full name, ID/passport number and name of the media house) to Nolizwi Magwagwa on 081 716 5824 or 021 403 2465 or nmagwagwa@parliament.gov.za.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA
